      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>Supporting research, public awareness, and advocacy for the political and human rights of East Turkistan, including the right of its people to decolonization, independence and national self-determination.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>East Turkistan Public Awareness Program: The organization conducted public education and awareness activities regarding Chinas ongoing genocide against Uyghurs and other Turkic peoples in East Turkistan. Activities included weekly public awareness rallies held in front of the White House and/or the U.S. Congress, online awareness advertising, and distribution of informational materials. These activities were intended to educate the public and increase awareness about China's ongoing campaign of colonization, genocide, and occupation in East Turkistan.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>4056</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>East Turkistan Congressional Advocacy Program: The organization conducted domestic advocacy activities focused on human rights conditions affecting Uyghurs and other Turkic peoples in East Turkistan. Activities included meetings with Members of Congress and congressional staff to provide information and raise awareness of China's ongoing campaign of colonization, genocide, and occupation in East Turkistan.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>981</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>East Turkistan International Advocacy Program: The organization conducted international advocacy activities related to China's ongoing genocide Uyghurs and other Turkic peoples in East Turkistan. Activities included meetings with government officials and non-governmental organizations in Japan, the United Kingdom, and the European Union. These efforts were aimed at increasing international awareness and engagement on East Turkistanrelated related issues.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>10357</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Grants and direct assistance totaling $30,434.75 were provided to support advocacy, education, and humanitarian relief related to East Turkistan. This included $15,699.00 in advocacy and rights grants, consisting of $8,053.00 awarded to the East Turkistan National Awakening Movement and $7,646.00 awarded to the East Turkistan Government in Exile Diplomacy &amp; Human Rights Office. In addition, $3,735.75 was awarded as educational support to East Turkistani students pursuing higher education, and $11,000.00 in direct humanitarian assistance was provided to East Turkistani concentration camp survivors, refugees, and victims of genocide.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>30435</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
