      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Part II-B, Line 1</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>During the tax year, the organization engaged in limited lobbying activities related to specific legislation and proposed legislative actions. Activities included advocacy related to the Uyghur Policy Act and efforts to encourage the introduction of congressional legislation or resolutions recognizing East Turkistan as an occupied country, promoting accountability for ongoing genocide, and supporting East Turkistans decolonization and national self-determination. Approximately 15% of certain program activities were allocable to lobbying. Grassroots lobbying consisted of a portion of U.S.-directed social media advertising ($302) and a portion of public rallies and demonstrations ($218) that included communications to the general public regarding these matters. Direct lobbying consisted of meetings with Members of Congress and congressional staff ($147). Total lobbying expenditures for the year were $667, representing a limited portion of the organizations overall exempt purpose activities.</ExplanationTxt>
